# Pre-push guards — kept fast (~30 sec total) so the dev loop stays
# tight. Heavier suites (full contract, integration, e2e, coverage) run
# in CI only.
#
# Rationale per check (all derived from 2026-05-17 polish retrospective):
#
#   - check:layout    : single-page → single-container invariant
#                       (Spec §FR-007 CLS-0). Cheap (~1 sec).
#
#   - check:fixme     : zero test.fixme + bare test.skip in
#                       tests/e2e + tests/contract. Closes the
#                       F4-ship-with-fixmes regression net erosion
#                       class. Cheap (~1 sec).
#
#   - vitest payments contract : F5R3 H-5 contract drift class —
#                       webhook Result<T,E> envelope +
#                       WebhookSignatureError mock importActual.
#                       Catches surface promise changes BEFORE merge.
#                       ~12 sec on Neon Singapore.
#
#   - vitest architecture     : Principle III Clean-Architecture
#                       barrel guard — events module barrel rule
#                       (e815caa9 F6 Phase 10 leaked raw infra).
#                       ~10 sec.
#
# Other tests/contract/* dirs (auth, broadcasts, events, members,
# plans, portal, renewals) run in full CI only — they're stable
# surfaces with no recent drift class to guard against in pre-push.

pnpm check:layout
pnpm check:fixme
pnpm vitest run tests/contract/ tests/unit/architecture/ --passWithNoTests
